    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-05T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-05T21:00:00-05:00" n="716"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/3794: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-06T11:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 6, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 6—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Our 706, November 5, 2 p.m.,<note n="38" xml:id="d716fn38">Not printed.</note>
                    reference Kuling situation. The Foreign Office states that instructions were
                    sent yesterday to the Japanese naval and military authorities at Kiukiang to
                    consult with American and British Commanders with a view to rendering
                    assistance.</p>
                <p>Sent to Hankow, repeated to Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
